article.description: Bryson scores 20 to help UCSB knock off UC Davis, 74-60
article.headline: Bryson scores 20 to help UCSB knock off UC Davis, 74-60
article.linkText: Bryson scores 20 to help UCSB knock off UC Davis, 74-60
article.story: SANTA BARBARA, Calif. -- Michael Bryson scored 20 and Alan Williams had 15 points and 16 rebounds to help UC Santa Barbara knock off Big West Conference-leading UC Davis 74-60 on Thursday night. John Green added 15 points for UCSB (15-12, 8-5). Williams, who also had four assists, two steals and four blocked shots, moved into fifth on the school's career scoring list with 1,616. He now has 12 double-doubles this season, despite missing seven games due to a shoulder injury. Corey Hawkins led UC Davis (21-5, 11-2) with 18 points and Josh Fox had 16. Two free throws and a jumper by Fox pulled Davis within four with 9:50 left but, following a technical foul, Zalmico Harmon hit a pair from the stripe and Williams made a jumper and UCSB led 57-49 eight minutes to go. Davis cut its deficit to six twice before a 9-2 run by the Gauchos put the game away.
